1 (h) "Public agency" has the same meaning as KRS 61.870, including a policy-
2 making board, or any officer, employee, or entity of a public institution
3 operating under KRS Chapter 164.
4 (2) No law enforcement agency, law enforcement officer, employee of a law
5 enforcement agency, public agency, public official, employee of a public agency, or
6 employee of a local government shall enforce, assist in the enforcement of, or
7 otherwise cooperate in the enforcement of a federal ban on firearms, ammunition,
8 or firearm accessories, and shall not participate in any federal enforcement action
9 implementing a federal ban on firearms, ammunition, or firearm accessories.
10 (3) No law enforcement agency, local government, or public agency shall adopt a rule,
11 order, ordinance, or policy under which the entity enforces, assists in the
12 enforcement of, or otherwise cooperates in a federal ban on firearms, ammunition,
13 or firearm accessories.
14 (4) No local government, employee of a local government, public official, public
15 agency, or employee of a public agency shall expend public funds or allocate
16 resources for the enforcement of a federal ban on firearms, ammunition, or firearm
17 accessories.
18 (5) A person commits an offense under this section when, while acting in his or her
19 official capacity under color of law, he or she knowingly violates this section. An
20 offense under this section is a Class B misdemeanor for the first offense and a Class
21 A misdemeanor for each subsequent offense.
22 (6) A person who knowingly commits an offense under this section shall be subject to
23 termination from employment to the extent allowable under state law.
24 (7) Nothing in this section may be interpreted to prohibit or otherwise limit a law
25 enforcement agency, law enforcement officer, employee of a law enforcement
26 agency, public agency, public official, employee of a public agency, or employee of
27 a local government from cooperating, communicating, or collaborating with a
